---
description: Testing conventions and patterns
globs: **/*.test.*, **/*.spec.*, **/test_*.*, **/*_test.*
---

- Write tests before or alongside implementation
- Structure: Arrange-Act-Assert (Given-When-Then)
- Name tests descriptively: test_<what>_<when>_<expected>
- Each test should be independent — no shared mutable state
- Mock external dependencies, not internal logic
- Cover edge cases: empty inputs, boundary values, errors
- Target 80%+ coverage; 100% for critical paths
- Keep test files colocated with source or in parallel test directory
